immutable SIEM collectors.\n   * **Non-Hardened Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)**: simulated frontend roles, needing a rigorous backend BOLA/privilege escalation audit.\n   * **Absence of File Scanning & Malware Filtering**: mocked document uploads bypass physical malware scanning.\n   * **Zero Payment Compliance Integration**: billing and invoice values computed dynamically from local db seed templates without PCI-DSS audits.\n3. **Phase 6 Enterprise Security Hardening Roadmap:**\n   * Migrating to **Production-Grade Persistence Engine** (AWS Aurora Serverless v2 PostgreSQL, SSL, RLS).\n   * Transitioning to **Hardened Cookie-Based Session Storage** (`HttpOnly`, `Secure`, `SameSite` flags).\n   * Implementing **Refresh Token Rotation (RTR)**.\n   * Establishing **Secure Password Reset Verification Workflows** (timed expiration, secure token delivery).\n   * Utilizing **Enterprise Identity Providers (SSO & MFA)** (Okta, Azure AD, SAML/OIDC, Google Authenticator).\n   * Deploying **Global API Gateways & Distributed Rate Limiting** (AWS WAF, Redis token-bucket).\n   * Designing **SIEM Integrations & Immutable Audit Ledgers** (JSON logs to CloudWatch/DataDog).\n   * Implementing **Secrets Vault Integrations** (AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault).\n   * Restructuring to **Secure Deployment Configurations & IaC Hardening** (Terraform, Docker slim non-root, TLS 1.3).\n   * Enforcing **CORS Hardening** (eliminating `*` wildcard, configuring strict HSTS/CSP security headers).\n4. **"}}
